# Frontend Conventions

> Frontend only. Project-wide rules: `.cursor/rules/core/`.
> See also: `architecture.mdc` · `api.mdc`

## Barrel `index.ts` in Every Slice

Every slice must have a root `index.ts` that serves as its public API.

```
features/create-todo/
├── api/
├── ui/
└── index.ts        # required — slice public API
```

## Import Through Slice Public API Only

Import from the public API of a slice or shared segment. Never reach into internal files.

| Layer                                      | Public API path    | Example                       |
| ------------------------------------------ | ------------------ | ----------------------------- |
| `features`, `entities`, `widgets`, `pages` | `@/layer/slice`    | `@/entities/todo`             |
| `shared`                                   | `@/shared/segment` | `@/shared/ui`, `@/shared/lib` |

The `shared` layer has no domain slices — its segments (`ui`, `lib`, `api`, `model`) are the public API entry points.

```ts
// ✅
import { CreateTodoForm, getTodos } from '@/features/create-todo';
import { TodoCard, useGetTodosQuery } from '@/entities/todo';
import { Button } from '@/shared/ui';

// ❌ — segment import (non-shared layers)
import { getTodos } from '@/entities/todo/api';

// ❌ — deep file import
import { CreateTodoForm } from '@/features/create-todo/ui/create-todo-form';
```

If something is missing from the public API — add it to the slice `index.ts`, do not import around it.

## Types in `types.ts`

Types and interfaces live in `types.ts` within the relevant segment or slice.

## Constants in `constants.ts`

`constants.ts` can live in both `model/` and `api/` segments. Do not mix domain and API constants.

| Segment      | Purpose                                               |
| ------------ | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| **`model/`** | Domain constants — statuses, limits, validation rules |
| **`api/`**   | API constants — React Query options, retry config     |

See `api.mdc` for API-specific usage.

## Segment Barrels — Internal Use Only

Use segment `index.ts` barrels **only inside the slice** when wiring the root `index.ts`. External code must never import from them.

## Deep Imports — Exceptions Only

Reaching into a slice from outside is allowed only in:

- `next.config.ts` / `tsconfig.json`
- Server fetch actions from `api/server/` (see `api.mdc` and `architecture.mdc`)

## Exports

Avoid `export default`. Use named exports and re-export via `index.ts`.

Exception: `export default` is allowed **only** in `page.tsx` and `layout.tsx` (Next.js requirement).

```tsx
// app/todos/page.tsx — allowed
export { TodosPage as default } from '@/pages/todos';
```

## Reuse Before Create

Before adding a utility or UI component, check `shared/ui`, `shared/lib`, and `shared/utils`. Do not duplicate existing helpers.

## Internationalization

All user-facing strings go through i18n (next-intl). See `architecture.mdc` for examples.
